<div class='communityQuestionSubTitle'>
Popular Answered Questions
</div>
<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/357973-i-enjoyed-seeing-how-the-various-lives-of">I enjoyed seeing how the various lives of the characters intertwined throughout the novel. However, it was not clear to me how the chapter &quot;Tag&quot; fit in with rest of the novel. The photographer did not reappear or connect with the other characters. Any ideas?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_357973'><a id="like_count_community_question_357973" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/357973?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">5 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F5941033-let-the-great-world-spin">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/357973-i-enjoyed-seeing-how-the-various-lives-of">6 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/357973-i-enjoyed-seeing-how-the-various-lives-of">See all 8 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/46310293-michael-lane"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1464730987i/46310293._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/46310293-michael-lane">Michael Lane</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    Like Noelia and Emily have already mentioned, you'll see Fernando's name if you read the credit for the photo that shows up (seemingly randomly insert<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    Like Noelia and Emily have already mentioned, you'll see Fernando's name if you read the credit for the photo that shows up (seemingly randomly inserted) after Tillie's chapter, which in turn is the one picture that Jaslyn carries with her in her chapter. <br /><br />I thought this was one of the deepest pieces of a book all about transience vs. permanence and the ties that bind. Several times New York is described as a place that is constantly reinventing itself, and so nothing is permanent. Philippe Petit's stunt, which could only have happened in New York, was purely transient by it's nature... yet, to this day, it lives on in the city's collective memory even though the actual Twin Towers (which should have been permanent) are no longer there.<br /><br />In "Tag", Fernando dreams of leaving his mark on the city, even if it means going far into the bowels of the subway tunnels to do it. In the end, his snapshot of Petit's walk documents a fleeting moment in history AND provides Jaslyn an enduring artifact that connects Jaslyn to a mother she never met. <br /><br />Fernando's chapter and the photo seem random at first glance but, in my opinion, they are the pieces that bring the whole story together!<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</span>
</div>
</div>
